<p>Assimptor requires the Assimp library to be installed on your system. It currently supports macOS only (both Apple Silicon and Intel).</p>

<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://lean-lang.org/">Lean 4</a> (v4.26.0+)</li>
  <li>Lake (included with Lean)</li>
  <li><a href="https://brew.sh/">Homebrew</a> (for installing Assimp)</li>
  <li>macOS with Clang compiler</li>
</ul>

<h3>Installing Assimp</h3>

<p>Install Assimp via Homebrew:</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash">brew install assimp</code></pre>

<p>This installs Assimp to <code>/opt/homebrew</code> (Apple Silicon) or <code>/usr/local</code> (Intel). The lakefile automatically searches both locations.</p>

<h3>Lakefile Configuration</h3>

<p>Add Assimptor to your <code>lakefile.lean</code>:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">require assimptor from git "https://github.com/nathanial/assimptor" @ "v0.1.0"</code></pre>

<h3>Building</h3>

<p>Assimptor includes native C++ code that must be compiled. Use the provided build script:</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash"># Navigate to your project
cd your-project/

# Build with the build script
./build.sh</code></pre>

<p>Or build manually by setting the Lean C compiler:</p>

<pre><code class="language-bash">LEAN_CC=/usr/bin/clang lake build</code></pre>

